.Dd January 28, 2026
.Dt DWLCTL 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm dwlctl
.Nd command-line client for the dwl IPC interface
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl h
.Op Fl s Ar path
.Ar command
.Op Ar args ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
communicates with a running
.Xr dwl 1
compositor over a Unix domain socket using a JSON-based IPC protocol.
It can query compositor state, invoke actions, and modify configuration
at runtime.
.Pp
All responses are printed to standard output as JSON objects containing
a
.Dq success
boolean field and either a
.Dq data
or
.Dq error
field.
.Nm
exits 0 on success or 1 on failure.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl h
Print usage information and exit.
.It Fl s Ar path
Override the IPC socket path.
By default,
.Nm
discovers the socket automatically (see
.Sx ENVIRONMENT ) .
.El
.Sh COMMANDS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Ic get Ar target
Query compositor state.
.Ar target
is one of:
.Bl -tag -width "keybinds" -offset indent -compact
.It Cm monitors
List all monitors with layout, geometry, gaps, and focus state.
.It Cm clients
List all clients with app_id, title, geometry, and window state.
.It Cm focused
Get the currently focused client, or null if none.
.It Cm config
Dump the current runtime configuration.
.It Cm keybinds
List all active keybindings.
.It Cm layouts
List available layout modes.
.El
.It Ic action Ar name Op Ar value ...
Invoke a compositor action by name.
Actions correspond to the functions available in keybinding configuration.
If multiple
.Ar value
arguments are given, they are passed as an array (used by
.Cm spawn ) .
.Pp
Available actions:
.Bl -tag -width "scroller_cycle_proportion" -offset indent -compact
.It Cm spawn Ar cmd ...
Launch a program.
.It Cm killclient
Close the focused window.
.It Cm quit
Exit the compositor.
.It Cm focusstack Ar n
Move focus up
.Pq Ar n Ns =\-1
or down
.Pq Ar n Ns =+1
the stack.
.It Cm focusdir Ar dir
Directional focus:
.Ar dir
is 0 (left), 1 (right), 2 (up), or 3 (down).
.It Cm zoom
Swap the focused client with the master.
.It Cm setmfact Ar delta
Adjust master area factor (e.g.\&
.Ar +0.05
or
.Ar \-0.05 ) .
.It Cm setlayout Ar layout
Set the layout.
.Ar layout
is one of
.Cm tile , floating , monocle , scroller ,
or a layout symbol.
.It Cm togglefloating
Toggle the focused window between tiled and floating.
.It Cm togglefullscreen
Toggle the focused window between normal and fullscreen.
.It Cm incnmaster Ar n
Increase or decrease the number of master windows.
.It Cm incgaps Ar n
Adjust all gaps.
.It Cm incigaps Ar n
Adjust inner gaps.
.It Cm incihgaps Ar n
Adjust inner horizontal gaps.
.It Cm incivgaps Ar n
Adjust inner vertical gaps.
.It Cm incogaps Ar n
Adjust outer gaps.
.It Cm incohgaps Ar n
Adjust outer horizontal gaps.
.It Cm incovgaps Ar n
Adjust outer vertical gaps.
.It Cm togglegaps
Toggle gaps on or off.
.It Cm defaultgaps
Reset gaps to default values.
.It Cm scroller_cycle_proportion Ar n
Cycle scroller column proportion
.Pq Ar n Ns =+1 or Ar n Ns =\-1 .
.It Cm consume_or_expel Ar n
Consume
.Pq Ar n Ns =0
or expel
.Pq Ar n Ns =1
a window in scroller layout.
.It Cm focusmon Ar dir
Move focus to another monitor.
.Ar dir
is
.Cm left
or
.Cm right .
.It Cm movetomon Ar dir
Move the focused window to another monitor.
.Ar dir
is
.Cm left
or
.Cm right .
.It Cm moveresize Ar mode
Begin interactive move
.Pq Cm move
or resize
.Pq Cm resize .
.It Cm chvt Ar n
Switch to virtual terminal
.Ar n .
.El
.It Ic set Ar key Ar value
Set a runtime configuration value.
.Ar key
and
.Ar value
correspond to settings in the
.Xr dwl 1
configuration file.
Changes take effect immediately.
.It Ic reload
Reload the configuration file from disk, equivalent to sending
.Dv SIGHUP
to the compositor.
.It Ic version
Print the compositor version.
.El
.Sh ENVIRONMENT
.Nm
locates the IPC socket using the following methods, in order of priority:
.Bl -enum -offset indent -compact
.It
The
.Fl s
option, if given.
.It
The
.Ev DWL_SOCK
environment variable, if set.
.It
.Pa $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/dwl-ipc.$WAYLAND_DISPLAY.sock
.El
.Pp
The
.Ev DWL_SOCK
variable is set automatically by
.Xr dwl 1
for child processes.
.Bl -tag -width WAYLAND_DISPLAY
.It Ev DWL_SOCK
Full path to the IPC Unix domain socket.
.It Ev XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
Base directory for user runtime files.
.It Ev WAYLAND_DISPLAY
Name of the Wayland display, used to construct the default socket path.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
List all monitors:
.Dl dwlctl get monitors
.Pp
Get the focused window:
.Dl dwlctl get focused
.Pp
Launch a terminal:
.Dl dwlctl action spawn alacritty
.Pp
Switch to monocle layout:
.Dl dwlctl action setlayout monocle
.Pp
Increase master factor:
.Dl dwlctl action setmfact 0.05
.Pp
Set border width to 2:
.Dl dwlctl set borderpx 2
.Pp
Reload configuration:
.Dl dwlctl reload
.Pp
Connect to a specific socket:
.Dl dwlctl -s /run/user/1000/dwl-ipc.wayland-1.sock get clients
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr dwl 1
